## Data Attribution

This project analyzes publicly available data from:

- **WHO MPOWER**: World Health Organization tobacco control policy data
  Source: https://www.who.int/data/gho

- **IHME GBD**: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation Global Burden of Disease Study
  Source: http://www.healthdata.org/gbd

- **World Bank WDI**: World Development Indicators
  Source: https://databank.worldbank.org/source/world-development-indicators

Users of this software should cite the original data sources appropriately in any
publications or presentations resulting from this analysis.

## Academic Use

This software was developed for academic research purposes studying the causal impact
of WHO MPOWER tobacco control policies on mortality outcomes using modern econometric
methods including Callaway & Sant'Anna (2021) staggered difference-in-differences.

If you use this code or methodology in your research, please consider citing:

```
MPOWER Mortality Causal Analysis (2025)
Causal inference analysis of WHO MPOWER tobacco control policies' impact on mortality outcomes
GitHub: https://github.com/jc7k/mpower-mortality-causal-analysis
```

## Methodology Attribution

This project implements methods from:

- Callaway, B., & Sant'Anna, P. H. (2021). Difference-in-differences with multiple time periods.
  Journal of Econometrics, 225(2), 200-230.

- Athey, S., & Imbens, G. W. (2017). The econometrics of randomized experiments.
  Handbook of Economic Field Experiments, 1, 73-140.
